</p><textarea readonly="" accesskey="," id="wpTextbox1" cols="80" rows="25" style="" class="mw-editfont-monospace" lang="en" dir="ltr" name="wpTextbox1">&lt;noinclude>{{Infobox/scenario&lt;/noinclude>
&lt;includeonly>{{Row/scenario&lt;/includeonly>
 |name=Evacuee
 |start_name=Evac Shelter
 |ident=evacuee
 |points=0
 |allowed_professions1=
 |restricted_professions1=
 |allowed_locs1=[[Evac shelter]]
 |map_special=
 |forced_traits1=
 |forbidden_traits1=
 |flags1=
 |description=You have survived the initial wave of panic, and have achieved (relative) safety in one of the many government evac shelters.
}}&lt;noinclude>
==Notes==
&lt;!-- *YOUR PERSONAL NOTES AND HINTS GO BELOW HERE* -->
*This is the default scenario, and seems to be the canon origin story of many survivors in-game.
*While you start in an [[evac shelter]], think carefully about these:
**Is the evac shelter vandalised beyond your repair skills?
**Is the city too dangerous to be near?
**Are there enough food and other supplies in the evac shelter?
**Is there a stable, safe source of water, such as a [[funnel]] and [[gallon jug]], in easy reach? If not, is a [[river]], [[lake]], or [[swamp]] easily accessible?
**Is there a monster hotspot (e.g., an [[anthill]], [[triffid grove]], [[fungal bloom]], [[fungal tower]], or group of [[fungal flowers]]) too near?
If you don't have many of these advantages, or the area is too dangerous, you should consider a new home to go to after you gather a few supplies from the city.

[[Category:scenario]]
